Let $BD = BE = x$ and $CF = CE = y$.  Then $BC = x + y = 23$.  Also, $AD = AB - BD = 25 - x$ and $AF = AC - CF = 25 - y$.  The perimeter of parallelogram $ADEF$ is $2(AD + AF) = 2(25 - x + 25 - y) = 2(50 - (x + y)) = 2(50 - 23) = \boxed{54}$.

